Driving License System

Full-stack app to manage applicants, applications, document uploads, and status tracking.

Tech Stack

Frontend: Angular 16+ (TypeScript)

Backend: Spring Boot 3+ (Java 17+), Spring Data JPA, Spring Validation

Database: MySQL 8.x

Build Tools: Maven, Angular CLI

Prerequisites

Node.js 18+ and npm

Angular CLI npm i -g @angular/cli

Java 17+

Maven 3.9+

MySQL 8.x (running locally)

Quick Start
# 1) clone
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/<your-repo>.git
cd <your-repo>

# 2) start backend (in one terminal)
cd backend
# configure application.properties (see below) then:
mvn spring-boot:run

# 3) start frontend (in another terminal)
cd ../frontend
npm install
# dev with API proxy (no CORS headaches):
npm start


Frontend dev: http://localhost:4200

Backend API: http://localhost:8080

Backend (Spring Boot)
1) Configure database

Create a DB (example: driving_license_db):

CREATE DATABASE driving_license_db CHARACTER SET utf8mb4 COLLATE utf8mb4_0900_ai_ci;

2) src/main/resources/application.properties
# ----- Server -----
server.port=8080

# ----- MySQL -----
spring.datasource.url=jdbc:mysql://localhost:3306/driving_license_db?useSSL=false&allowPublicKeyRetrieval=true&serverTimezone=UTC
spring.datasource.username=root
spring.datasource.password=your_password
spring.datasource.driver-class-name=com.mysql.cj.jdbc.Driver

# ----- JPA / Hibernate -----
spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto=update
spring.jpa.show-sql=true
spring.jpa.properties.hibernate.format_sql=true

# ----- File upload (optional) -----
spring.servlet.multipart.max-file-size=50MB
spring.servlet.multipart.max-request-size=50MB

# ----- CORS (optional if using Angular proxy) -----
app.cors.allowed-origins=http://localhost:4200

Run the backend
mvn clean spring-boot:run

for front end
npm install

npm start
